author: Slidebean
description:
Humanoid robots aren’t fully autonomous yet.

The 1X NEO robot, set to ship next year, still requires a human operator in VR for many basic tasks.
In WSJ’s live test, the “AI powered” robot struggled with chores like loading a dishwasher.
This hybrid model part robot, part remote worker and might be the bridge between robotics today and true autonomy.
But it also raises big questions about privacy, cost, and expectations.

👉Hear the full breakdown on The Slidebean Stand-Up; streaming now on Spotify, Apple Podcasts, and all major podcast platforms.
title: Inside the illusion of autonomy in robotics

author: Slidebean
description:
AI startups are burning millions every hour.

Building AI isn’t just hard, it’s insanely expensive.
Cursor spent $70M on AWS this year. Anthropic? $1.3B in 2024.
That’s $3.7M a day, or $155K an hour, just in cloud bills.
The reality: AI companies raise billions, only to hand it right back to AWS, Google, or Azure.
In the AI gold rush, the cloud is the shovel store and it’s charging by the minute.

👉Hear the full breakdown on The Slidebean Stand-Up; streaming now on Spotify, Apple Podcasts, and all major podcast platforms.
title: The real money in AI is flowing to the cloud
